13/10/21, 1:51 pm - Agrah DS: HELLO ASPIRING ENGINEER
 
It's our autonomous feeling to express you that you have successfully registered for the RECRUITMENT DRIVE 2021 OF SAE AKGEC.
Now according to our progressive procedure you have to attempt online assessment (test).
 
 Here are some rules and regulations regarding the first round of RECRUITMENT PROCESS which is going to take place on 13th of October, 2021.
 
1) If you wish to participate in multiple domain then you can write all your chosen domain in preferences column and attempt the test of those domains.
2) Test will be of 30 minutes and you have to submit it within the given time frame.
3) Time slots for each domain is :
·        For Mechanical domain - 5:30 p.m. to 6:00 p.m.
Test Link - https://forms.gle/aXSmw1F6Es8zVxrYA
·        For Innovation domain - 6:15 p.m. to 6:45 p.m.
Test Link - https://forms.gle/B2t7eFGhidggofXM7
·        For Designing and Media domain - 7:00 p.m. to 7:30 p.m.
Test Link - https://forms.gle/WsSHBp1FN1Z2nU5D6 
4) You should make sure that you are available at your given time slots.
5) The Google form link will be activated accordingly and hence you are allowed to give the exam in the given slot.
6) Those who belong to mechanical branch & selected Innovation or media domain are required to give test of mechanical domain also.
7) Those who belong to branch other than mechanical & selected mechanical as their domain are required to give test of Innovation or media domain also.
 
In case of any issue kindly contact our coordinators :

26/10/21, 12:54 pm - Agrah DS: Greetings Techno Freaks,

Team ISTE, a student chapter of AKGEC is back with the most awaited event of the year "EXQUIZITE 2021". This year not only will it be fun and interactive, but also more passionate and more challenging. The only question is Do you have what it takes.

EXQUIZITE 2021 will be held in 3 rounds:

Round 1
The first round of the event is a pictorial quiz round. Each team will be given a stipulated amount of time to answer questions based on picture identification or general questions based on the pictures shown. The pictures will consist of categories(eg-brands, technology, etc.)

Round 2
The second round of the event is a Spell Bee. It will consist of words that will have you perplexed and the team will have to spell them in a given time. 

Round 3
The third and final round of the event is a Brainteaser round. It will consist of questions which the students will have to answer in a given amount of time.

Each team should have two members only. Registration fee for the same is 100/per team.


Remember, the secret of success is to always be ready so fasten your seat belts and wake up that nerd in you. This is the journey you don't wanna miss.

The link for the registration form for the EXQUIZITE 2021 is given:
https://forms.gle/dwWm1GB9E71GXAaK7

The deadline for registering yourself is 27 October 2021 till 12:00 am

Coordinators:

Manya Singh
7520339205

Vaibhav Garg
8587070792

Abhishek Vishwakarma
8799131958

For any queries, you may contact our coordinators.

Best Wishes, 

ISTE, the student chapter of AKGEC

16/11/21, 10:08 pm - Vanshika Akg: Dear Students,
AKGEC IDEA Lab is organising STARTUP CONCLAVE-2021 on 29th-30th November 2021 for B.Tech Students.  Both on-going start-ups and students with new innovative ideas can participate to win the seed funding and get the opportunity to incubate their Startup/Innovative Idea with IDEA Lab.
 
This conclave is aimed to bring and nurture the best innovative ideas and start-ups from the college and to offer the platform for exploring the world of entrepreneurship and to start new ventures with an aid provided by our college. Main objective of this STARTUP CONCLAVE is to motivate and assist prospective and potential entrepreneurs. This drive focuses on the best budding start-ups of our college to get good public exposure and will make sure that equal opportunity will be provided to all.
 
Key benefit for Start-up:
•       Work space equipped with office furniture, computer systems, internet etc, in college campus.
•       Initial Grant Rs.10,000 to all the selected Idea/Startups.
•       Seed funding upto 3,00,000/- for selected startup (subjected to their performance after probation period).
•       Mentorship sessions by experts in the field of Innovation, Entrepreneurship, IPR and Incubation.
•       Mentoring support for startups to convert their idea to POC and POC to prototype.
 
Team Leader can register using the link: https://forms.gle/9U3JVaCWo7b8wWhC6
Last Date to Register – 27/11/2021
 
Certificate and PC will be provided to all students participating in STARTUP CONCLAVE.
 
For any query you may contact to IDEA Lab Student Coordinators:
  1. Prakhar Mishra - 7424904255
  2. Krati Gupta - 7290059444
 
Opportunities are like sunrises. If you wait too long, you miss them. Jump in with both feet, and seize this opportunity. Gear up and take your first step towards becoming a successful entrepreneur by registering in the Conclave.
 
We are looking forward for your active participation. 
 
Best of luck!
Team IDEA Lab
AKGEC

18/11/21, 8:03 pm - Nikhil DS: Dear Students,
AKGEC IDEA Lab is organising STARTUP CONCLAVE-2021 on 29th-30th November 2021 for B.Tech Students.  Both on-going start-ups and students with new innovative ideas can participate to win the seed funding and get the opportunity to incubate their Startup/Innovative Idea with IDEA Lab.
 
This conclave is aimed to bring and nurture the best innovative ideas and start-ups from the college and to offer the platform for exploring the world of entrepreneurship and to start new ventures with an aid provided by our college. Main objective of this STARTUP CONCLAVE is to motivate and assist prospective and potential entrepreneurs. This drive focuses on the best budding start-ups of our college to get good public exposure and will make sure that equal opportunity will be provided to all.
 
Key benefit for Start-up:
•       Work space equipped with office furniture, computer systems, internet etc, in college campus.
•       Initial Grant Rs.10,000 to all the selected Idea/Startups.
•       Seed funding upto 3,00,000/- for selected startup (subjected to their performance after probation period).
•       Mentorship sessions by experts in the field of Innovation, Entrepreneurship, IPR and Incubation.
•       Mentoring support for startups to convert their idea to POC and POC to prototype.
 
Team Leader can register using the link: https://forms.gle/9U3JVaCWo7b8wWhC6
Last Date to Register – 27/11/2021
 
Certificate and PC will be provided to all students participating in STARTUP CONCLAVE.
 
For any query you may contact to IDEA Lab Student Coordinators:
  1. Prakhar Mishra - 7424904255
  2. Krati Gupta - 7290059444
 
Opportunities are like sunrises. If you wait too long, you miss them. Jump in with both feet, and seize this opportunity. Gear up and take your first step towards becoming a successful entrepreneur by registering in the Conclave.
 
We are looking forward for your active participation. 
 
Best of luck!
Team IDEA Lab
AKGEC

Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Technical University, Uttar Pradesh (formerly Uttar Pradesh Technical University) Sector-11 Janakipuram Extension, Sitapur Road, Lucknow-226031

Letter No: AKTU / P.N. / 2021 / 5207

Date: 23rd November, 2021

To,

Director / Principal,

All the institutions affiliated to Dr. A.P.J. Abdul Kalam Technical University, Lucknow.

Subject: Regarding the examination to be conducted by the university in the odd semester 2021-22.

Sir, regarding the above subject, it is to be informed that due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the studies of the students studying in the institutions affiliated to the university have been greatly affected. Due to which many problems have been faced in getting their examinations done on time. Therefore, in order to bring continuity in the study and examination of the students by the University, according to the decision taken by the University Examination Committee in item number 73.13 of the meeting held on 22/11/2021, except the first and third semester courses in which lateral entry takes place. The examinations of all semesters will be conducted from the last week of December, 2021. Apart from the above, the examinations of the courses in which admission is done in lateral entry will start from the last week of February 2022.

Kindly being aware of the above, informing all the students and taking necessary action.

Make trouble

Sincerely,

But 23/11/2

(Prof. Anuram Tripathi)

examination controller

Endorsement Number & Date: Above

Copy: For information and necessary action to the following. 1. Registrar / Finance Officer, AKTU. Lucknow. Joint / Deputy Controller of Examinations (S) / Deputy Controller of Examinations (D). AKTU, Lucknow.

2

3.

4.

In-charge ERP AKTU, Lucknow for necessary action. Staff Officer, Vice Chancellor's Office, AKTU, Lucknow as Hon'ble Vice Chancellor

For perusal Media in-charge AKTU. Lucknow. 5.

6.

Shri Pawan Tripathi, Public Relations Officer, AKTU, Lucknow.

(Prof. Anurag Tripathi) Controller of Examinations

07/12/21, 4:45 pm - +91 83768 68855: <Media omitted>
07/12/21, 4:45 pm - +91 83768 68855: "Creativity is the greatest rebellion in existence. "

Let's steer the wheel of creativity and sail our ship towards a ragging free campus that stimulates the growth of young minds. Team Footprints welcomes you aboard to join the Anti-ragging poster making competition at ME block on December 8, 2021.

Time to dip your brushes in reds and blues and smear the strokes of virtue and nobility. Let's campaign together and spread awareness about the ill effects of ragging through our artistries.

You can register for the same on the registration desks which are set up at BB shed and CS-IT block or also online through Google forms.

The rules and regulations of the event and registration are as follows:

1. The team can consist of maximum of 2 members, but only one person on the team has to register for the event. Inter-branch and inter-year team can also participate. 
2. Resources would be provided at the venue.
3. Refrain from bringing cellphones.
4. Certificates and cash prizes will be rewarded to the winners and the best entries will be featured on the Arcade.
For any further queries, please contact the coordinators:
Mohit Kumar Singh (85271 72366)
Rifa Fatima
Prerit Mishra (75052 54493)

Link: https://bit.ly/3DxLmqm

From AKGEC: Ajay Kumar Garg Engineering College, Ghaziabad to Kedarnath Road via NH 7.

9 hr 2 min (396 km)
9 hr 2 min in current traffic

2. Exit the roundabout
3. Turn left toward AH2
4. Slight right toward AH2
5. Turn right toward AH2
6. Turn left onto AH2
7. Keep left to stay on AH2
8. Turn left

10. Merge with AH2
11. Take the ramp on the right to NE 3
12. Take the exit on the right toward Meerut Bypass Rd/NH 34
13. Slight right
14. Slight right onto NH334
15. Keep right to continue on NH334/NH 34
16. Slight left
17. Slight right at Bhoopatwala - Khadkhadi Rd/Haridwar- Motichur Rd ( Old Rishikesh Main Rd)
18. Slight right toward NH 34
19. Continue straight past Jaya Ram Ashram onto NH 34
20. Slight right to stay on NH 34
21. Turn right onto NH 34/NH 7
22. Turn right to stay on NH 7
23. Continue straight past Khaliyo Market
24. Slight left
25. Turn right onto NH 7
26. Slight left onto Rudraprayag Bypass Rd
27. Turn left toward NH107
28. Turn left onto NH107
29. Turn left
30. Turn left onto NH107
31. Keep left
32. Turn left onto NH107
33. Arrive at location: Kedarnath Road

09/01/22, 11:19 am - +91 93685 17639: Dear Students, 

In view of the the possibility of swift rise in the number of COVID cases in NCR,  the college has decided to suspend physical classes and start on-line classes for I and II year B Tech, M Tech and I year MCA students with effect from Monday, 10 Jan 2022. The revised Time Table for online classes will be issued by  respective HODs. 

The college will resume physical Classes/ Labs from 31 January 2022, followed by PUT and End Semester exams. Change in this date of reopening, if any, based on prevailing situation and directives from the AKTU/ State Govt, will be intimated to you. 

Students desirous of continuing to live in the hostel beyond 11 January may give their names to their Hostel Warden and can also attend physical classes. 

All are advised to follow all safety norms and precautions.  

Stay safe and healthy. 

Dr R K Agarwal
Director General

07/02/22, 12:22 pm - Kavyanshi DS: Dear All, 



In accordance with the University directive, it is decided to re-open the college in physical mode from 14th February 2022 (Monday). The ongoing academic activities including Sessional Examinations of 1st year, Pre-University Examinations of 2nd Year and regular classes of 3rd and 4th year will keep on going in on-line mode till 11th February 2022.  However, from 14th February 2022 all these academic activities will be held in off-line/physical mode. The hostels will be made available for occupation from 12th February 2022 (Saturday).

 

Variation in the examination schedule, if any, will be communicated through Dean Examinations separately. The revision class between Pre-University Tests schedule for 2nd year students, as already notified through respective departments, will remain undisturbed and will also convert to physical mode from 14 February 2022.

 

We are all looking forward to your return to college and resumption of normal college activities which have been curtailed and restricted due to Covid-19 since last two years. While the cases of Omicron are showing a declining trend, it is advised to keep taking proper precautions and raise our safety guards. Wearing mask, hand sanitization and adherence to Covid appropriate behaviour is to be strictly followed in the college for everyone’s safety.

while n!=-1:
	n=int(input("Please input next number\n"))
	maximum=max(maximum,n)
print ("maximum is:", maximum)

06/06/22, 8:56 pm - Akash DS: start = 25
end = 50
print("Prime numbers between", start, "and", end, "are:")

for num in range(start,end+1):
    # all prime numbers are greater than 1
    # if number is less than or equal to 1, it is not prime
    if num>1:
        for i in range(2,num):
            # check for factors
            if (num%i)==0:
                # not a prime number so break inner loop and
                # look for next number
                break
        else:
            print(num)

10/06/22, 9:44 am - +91 70801 08538: Dear All,

Aspire Institute’s mission is to transform the lives of low-income, first-generation college students around the world, at scale, through a fully funded leadership development program that enables them to make a positive impact in all aspects of human endeavour. This program is for students who are from backgrounds of social and financial adversity.

All applicants must meet the following criteria:

➢ First-generation to attend university, meaning their parents did not complete an undergraduate degree

➢ B. Tech I and II year

 ➢ Ages 18-26

Through the program, students will benefit:

➢ Gain access to fully funded HarvardX courses and leadership development tools.

 ➢ Participate in live seminars with Harvard and world-class faculty.

➢ Exchange ideas in a virtual classroom with a global community of peers.

Students who apply and are eligible will begin moving through the stages. Whether students complete one stage or all five, they will gain skills and certificates along the way. Once accepted to the Aspire Leaders Program, students will continue through a multi-stage selection process, culminating in the finalist program in October, virtually.

Interested and eligible students need to fill the following Google form by 3 PM, 7 June 2022.

Link for I year students: https://forms.gle/ihi6HEpfB7R7XpM29

Link for II year students: https://forms.gle/ZmsG5Tf5KLrzmSQM8

Program 2:


def test(a):

    def add(b):

        nonlocal a

        a += 1

        print("value of 'a' in inner function = ",a)

        print("value of 'b' in inner function = ",b)

        return a+b

    return add(b)

a=4

b=2

print("sum of a and b =",test(a))


Program 3:


mycode = 'print("hello world")'

code = """

def mutiply(x,y):

    return x*y

print("('Multiply of 2 and 3 is: ',",mutiply(2,3),end=')')

"""

exec(mycode)

exec(code)

Program 4:


def make_bold(fn):

    def wrapped():

        return "<b>" + fn() + "</b>"

    return wrapped


def make_italic(fn):

    def wrapped():

        return "<i>" + fn() + "</i>"

    return wrapped


def make_underline(fn):

    def wrapped():

        return "<u>" + fn() + "</u>"

    return wrapped

@make_bold

@make_italic

@make_underline

def hello():

    return "hello world"

print(hello()) ## returns "<b><i><u>hello world</u></i></b>"



Program 5:


l=[]

def printValues():

    for i in range(1,21):

        l.append(i**2)

    print(l)

   

printValues()

20/06/22, 10:41 pm - Chandan DS: class Circle():
    def __init__(self, r):
        self.radius = r

    def area(self):
        return self.radius**2*3.14
    
    def perimeter(self):
        return 2*self.radius*3.14

NewCircle = Circle(8)
print("Area = ",NewCircle.area())
print("Perimeter = ",NewCircle.perimeter())

20/06/22, 10:41 pm - Chandan DS: class py_solution:
 def threeSum(self, nums):
        nums, result, i = sorted(nums), [], 0
        while i < len(nums) - 2:
            j, k = i + 1, len(nums) - 1
            while j < k:
                if nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k] < 0:
                    j += 1
                elif nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k] > 0:
                    k -= 1
                else:
                    result.append([nums[i], nums[j], nums[k]])
                    j, k = j + 1, k - 1
                    while j < k and nums[j] == nums[j - 1]:
                        j += 1
                    while j < k and nums[k] == nums[k + 1]:
                        k -= 1
            i += 1
            while i < len(nums) - 2 and nums[i] == nums[i - 1]:
                i += 1
        return result

print(py_solution().threeSum([-25, -10, -7, -3, 2, 4, 8, 10]))
20/06/22, 10:41 pm - Chandan DS: class py_solution:
   def is_valid_parenthese(self, str1):
        stack, pchar = [], {"(": ")", "{": "}", "[": "]"}
        for parenthese in str1:
            if parenthese in pchar:
                stack.append(parenthese)
            elif len(stack) == 0 or pchar[stack.pop()] != parenthese:
                return False
        return len(stack) == 0

print("(){}[]  ",py_solution().is_valid_parenthese("(){}[]"))
print("()[{)}  ",py_solution().is_valid_parenthese("()[{)}"))
print("()  ",py_solution().is_valid_parenthese("()"))

04/07/22, 7:18 pm - Arnav DS: #2
def bubbleSort(alist):
    swapped = False
    for num in range(len(alist)-1,0,-1):
        for i in range(num):
            if alist[i] > alist[i + 1]:
                swapped = True
                # swapping data if the element is less than next element in the array
                alist[i], alist[i + 1] = alist[i + 1], alist[i]       
        if not swapped:
            # exiting the function if we didn't make a single swap
            # meaning that the array is already sorted.
            return

# list of elements
alist = [56,21,97,18,74,38,14,65,2]

# pass the list in bubbleSort function for sorting
bubbleSort(alist)

# print sorted list
print(alist)
04/07/22, 7:18 pm - Arnav DS: #3......
def insertionSort(alist):
   for i in range(1, len(alist)):
        key = alist[i]
        j = i-1
        while j >=0 and key < alist[j] :
                alist[j+1] = alist[j]
                j -= 1
        alist[j+1] = key

# list of elements
alist = [51,16,43,57,67,21,64,75,20]

# pass list to insertionSort function for sorting
insertionSort(alist)

# print the sorted list
print(alist)
04/07/22, 7:18 pm - Arnav DS: #5...
def fib(n) :
    if n==0 :
        return 0
    elif n ==1 :
        return 1
    else :
        return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)

num=10
print("printing first ",num," terms of fibonacci series")
for i in range(0,num):
    print(fib(i),end=",")

04/07/22, 8:24 pm - +91 91700 95600: def selection_sort(array):  
    length = len(array)  
      
    for i in range(length-1):  
        minIndex = i  
          
        for j in range(i+1, length):  
            if array[j]>array[minIndex]:  
                minIndex = j  
                  
        array[i], array[minIndex] = array[minIndex], array[i]  
          
          
    return array      
array = [5, 3, 2, 1, 4]  
print("Given list =",array)  
print("List after selection sort=",selection_sort(array))

14/09/22, 12:29 pm - Satyaprakash DS: SELECT * FROM EMP;
SELECT EMPNO,SAL FROM EMP;
SELECT  EMPNO,DEPTNO,MGR FROM EMP;
SELECT  ENAME FROM EMP WHERE DEPTNO=20;
SELECT ENAME,SAL FROM EMP WHERE SAL>1000;
SELECT EMPNO,JOB,ENAME FROM EMP WHERE JOB='MANAGER';
SELECT JOB,ENAME FROM EMP WHERE JOB='CLERK';
SELECT ENAME,JOB FROM EMP WHERE JOB='ANALYST' OR JOB='SALESMAN';
SELECT ENAME,JOB FROM EMP WHERE JOB!='MANAGER';
SELECT DISTINCT JOB FROM EMP;
SELECT ENAME FROM EMP WHERE COMM IS NULL;
SELECT ENAME FROM EMP WHERE COMM IS NULL AND SAL>2000;
SELECT ENAME,SAL,SAL*0.1 AS PF_AMOUNT FROM EMP;

For our Junkyard warriors.

An event where we embrace the value of waste, which makes us realise that the waste has a value, if it is placed at right place.

“Every Junkyard has a story to tell…….So tell us your story by joining us in the event”

                 Location- Mechanical Lawn
                 Round 2- 1st Dec
